"Answer","text":"Yes. Once a tooth root is gone, the surrounding jawbone usually starts shrinking because it is no longer being stimulated the way it was when the tooth was present."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is grafting always necessary after an extraction?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Some sites heal well without grafting, while others benefit from socket preservation to support a cleaner future implant or bridge plan. It depends on the tooth, the bone, and the long-term plan."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I get an implant immediately after extraction?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sometimes. In the right case, an implant can be placed the same day as the extraction. In other cases, it is safer to graft first and let the site heal before implant placement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens if I wait years to replace a tooth?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The site can lose bone, nearby teeth can drift, the opposing tooth can over-erupt, and the bite can change. Treatment is often still possible later, but it may be more complex and more expensive."}}]}</script><script type="application/ld+json" data-schema="breadcrumb">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://www.elmridgedental.com/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Missing Tooth Consequences","item":"https://www.elmridgedental.com/what-happens-if-you-dont-replace-a-missing-tooth"}]}</script><script type="application/ld+json" data-schema="missing-tooth-service">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Service","name":"Missing Tooth Replacement Consultation","url":"https://www.elmridgedental.com/what-happens-if-you-dont-replace-a-missing-tooth","description":"Evaluation and treatment planning for missing teeth, bone loss, grafting, and replacement options in Killeen, TX.","provider":{"@id":"https://www.elmridgedental.com/#dentist"},"areaServed"